I’m diving into the implementation of `IsInStaticInitContext`. It seems to return true for call expressions that trace back to an ArrowFunctionExpression without hitting a ScriptFunction. I should note a critical gap regarding async lambda calls since the spec says they share semantics with Async Functions, meaning if there's a compile-time error for async functions used in static initialization, it likely applies to async lambdas too. I wonder if `sig->Function()->IsAsyncFunc()` will confirm this for async lambdas — it probably does. However, there are no tests to back this up, which might be a concern. Also, what about async constructors? None found either."}]}

